\f0\fs24 \cf0 Today is the anniversary of the death of 
\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Daniel Gabriel Fahrenheit
\f0\b0  \cf4 (\cf2 1686 -1736), a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physicist"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 physicist}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inventor"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 inventor}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_instrument"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 scientific instrument}} maker. \
\
Fahrenheit was born in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Danzig"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Danzig}} (now \cf4 in\cf2  Poland), but lived most of his life in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dutch_Republic"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Dutch Republic}} (1701\'961736) and was one of the notable figures in the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dutch_Golden_Age"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 Golden Age of Dutch science and technology}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 A pioneer of exact thermometry,
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super  
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub he helped lay the foundations for the era of precision thermometry by inventing the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mercury-in-glass_thermometer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mercury-in-glass thermometer}} (first practical, accurate {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermometer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 thermometer}}) and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fahrenheit_scale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Fahrenheit scale}} (first standardized {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temperature_scale"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 temperature scale}} to be widely used). In other words, Fahrenheit's inventions ushered in the first revolution in the history of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermometry"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 thermometry}} (branch of physics concerned with methods of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temperature_measurement"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 temperature measurement}}). 
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \
\

\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub According to Fahrenheit's 1724 article, he determined his scale by reference to three fixed points of temperature. The lowest temperature was achieved by preparing a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frigorific_mixture"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 frigorific mixture}} of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ice"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 ice}}, water, and a salt and waiting for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eutectic_system"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 eutectic system}} to reach equilibrium temperature. The thermometer's reading there was taken as 0\'a0\'b0F. \
The second reference point was selected as the reading of the thermometer when it was placed in still water when ice was just forming on the surface. This was assigned as 32\'a0\'b0F. The third calibration point, taken as 96\'a0\'b0F, was selected as the thermometer's reading when the instrument was placed under the arm or in the mouth.\cf2 \cb1 \
\cf2 \cb3 \
The Fahrenheit scale was the primary temperature standard for climatic, industrial and medical purposes in English-speaking countries until the 1970s, nowadays replaced by the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celsius"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Celsius}} scale long used in the rest of the world.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super \
\
\'c8 oggi l\'92anniversario della morte di Daniel Gabriel Fahrenheit, fisico, ingegnere e inventore polacco ma di cultura tedesca. Ha inoltre speso la maggior parte della sua vita in Olanda contribuendo alla cosiddetta \'93epoca d\'92oro della scienza e tecnologia olandese\'94 \
\'c8 Considerato come l\'92inventore della termometria, la scienza che si occupa della misurazione esatta delle temperature ed ha dato fondamentali contributi allo sviluppo delle misurazioni termometriche. Il suo nome \'e9 tuttora legato a doppio filo
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  ad una scala termometrica che fu ampiamente utilizzata soprattutto nei paesi anglosassoni (\'e8 ancora ufficialmente usata negli {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stati_Uniti_d%27America"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 Stati Uniti}}). \'c8 meglio conosciuto per aver inventato il {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/Termometro_a_mercurio"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 termometro a mercurio}} ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://it.wikipedia.org/wiki/1714"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 1714}}).\
